message: Q2 of 2016 is already here. Did you make any dreams come true in the last 3 months? Got any ideas about what’s coming next? Share how ZTE tech helps you achieve your ambitions in the comments!

The Hoops for Kids mobile device donation drive was a big success! We were honored to partner with the Golden State Warriors to help Bay Area kids live, learn and play for the 2nd year. bit.ly/1qdkabd

We’re honored to be named #47 in the 2016 BrandZ™ Top 100 Most Valuable Chinese Brands for the second year in a row. Our brand value grew 46% over the last year! bit.ly/1pZHXLN

This year eHealthcare will get a boost when ZTE, the Health Department of the city of Düsseldorf and Telefónica Deutschland launch the first German open living lab for healthy ageing and smart home in Düsseldorf. http://bit.ly/1Lq9yzB

Our senior vice president, Pang Shengqing, delivered a keynote address on Smart City development and solutions at CeBIT 2016. Smart City is an ecosphere that requires input from everyone – we’re proud to help bring people together and move forward! #CeBIT http://bit.ly/21uSKZS

The human body and the IoT were made for each other. Today, we released mHealth, an all-in-one physical exam terminal for home and professional use. Your next family doctor could live in the cloud. bit.ly/1pl7EFP #CeBIT
What will living in a Smart City really be like? CeBIT attendees can find out for themselves at our interactive experience in the ZTE booth. bit.ly/1pGkK0Q
We’ve stepped up our game this year and are going to bring Pre5G to more than 10 countries in 2016. Will it be a slam dunk? Absolutely. bit.ly/1QvqRzg

At CES 2016, the ZTE booth is hosting cutting edge technology and famous faces from the NBA. NBA legends Scottie Pippen and Larry Johnson are here – ZTE USA CEO Cheng Lixin even got a selfie with Scottie Pippen! Outside CES, the Z-Car caused a stir as people lined up to check out the unique car that’s been traveling around America to spread the word about Z-Community! bit.ly/1Rkz0Ij

ZTE’s strong presence at CES is bolstered by the debut of two affordable premium devices, the Grand X 3 and the Avid Plus, the launch of Z Community, a member-led forum that will help develop a community sourced mobile device *and* Passport 2.0 for Axon, which includes unlimited out of warranty repairs and total assistance that supports device upgrades, replacement, shipping and set up! http://bit.ly/1JX5Fvw

ZTE is gearing up for CES 2016 in Las Vegas, fresh off a very successful 2015! Last year, 100 million ZTE mobile devices were shipped worldwide. We were ranked among the Top 6 smartphone manufacturers globally and in the Top 5 LTE smartphone manufacturers globally. Come see us (and the 2015 NBA Championship trophy – plus a few NBA stars!) at CES this year. We'll be in South Hall 3, Booth 31706. http://bit.ly/1TBHJU1
ZTE believes in the positive, transformative power of tech. In 2016, what technology do you think will have the biggest (or most surprising!) impact on your daily life?
